main event: Multiple UFO sightings reported in Dayton, Ohio from 1963 to 1965, including a stationary object and two luminous objects moving slowly.
interesting points: The first sighting involved one stationary object observed for one hour,The second sighting consisted of two white, luminous objects traveling at a constant altitude,The first sighting concluded as astronomical (stars),The second sighting was classified as unidentified and was observed for 2 minutes,The reports generated no photographs or physical evidence.
sighted object: One stationary object and two luminous objects
witness description: A civilian witness reported the sightings and filled out the questionnaire for the Air Force.
